      description : "TCAT-AS-001320 - Multifactor certificate-based tokens (CAC) must be used when accessing the management interface."
      info        : "Password authentication does not provide sufficient security control when accessing a management interface. DOD has specified that a CAC will be used when authenticating and passwords will only be used when CAC authentication is not a plausible solution. Tomcat provides the ability to do certificate based authentication and client authentication; therefore, the Tomcat server must be configured to use CAC.

